ZCZC OE18
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 302300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING LOW PRESSURE CENTRED OVER SERN SWEDEN 995 WILL MOV
SLWY SE WHILST FLN BEFORE LOSING ITS IDENTITY DURING MONDAY. MEANTIME A
RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE LYING FM ROCKALL TO SE ICELAND WILL MOV SLWY SE TO
BE LYING FM SHANNON TO FAIR ISLE BY MIDDAY MONDAY THEN INTO THE N SEA ON
TUESDAY. HIGH PRESSURE CENTRES WILL FORM IN THE SERN N SEA AND IN BISCAY
ON TUESDAY NIGHT CENTRED NEAR GERMAN BIGHT AND OVER SERN FRANCE BY WEDNESDAY
NIGHT. DURING WEDNESDAY AN ATLANTIC LOW WILL APPROACH WERN SEA AREAS. WEAK
LOW PRESSURE WILL BE SLOW MOV OVER ICELAND THROUGH MUCH OF THIS PERIOD. STRG
WINDS ARE POSS IN FAIR ISLE ON SUNDAY EVENING. OTHERWISE NO STRG WINDS ARE
EXP UNTIL LATER WEDNESDAY WHEN STRG WINDS ARE LIKELY TO DEVELOP IN SHANNON
AND ROCKALL AND STRG WINDS MAY DEVELOP IN LUNDY FASTNET AND IRISH SEA
